Right to Opt-Out of Data Sale
Under applicable laws, such as the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), you have the right to opt-out of the "sale" of your personal data. While Big Alpha Games does not sell personal data in the traditional sense (e.g., exchanging data for money), certain data-sharing activities for targeted advertising may be considered a "sale" under these laws.
How to Opt-Out of Data Sale or Sharing
You can opt-out of data sharing or sale by using one of the following methods:
In-App Privacy Controls:
Open the app, navigate to the "Privacy Settings" section(if available), and select the "Opt-Out of Data Sale" option.
Contact Us:
You can email us at
privacy@bigalphagames.com
with the subject line "Opt-Out Request." Include your account details (e.g., username or email associated with the app) in your request.
Additional Information
Once you opt-out, we will cease sharing your personal data for purposes that may qualify as a "sale" under applicable laws. However, you may still see advertisements in our apps, but they will not be personalized or targeted based on your preferences or activity.
If you have any questions or need further assistance, please contact our Data Protection Officer at
dpo@bigalphagames.com
or +92 334 4771226.
Caregiver's Rights Regarding Their Child's Personal Information
As a caregiver, you hold specific rights concerning the personal information we collect from your child. Below, we detail these rights and how to exercise them.
1. Caregiver Right to Stop the Collection or Use of Their Child's Personal Information
How Caregivers Can Stop the Collection or Use of Their Child's Personal Information
We fully acknowledge and respect the right of caregivers to manage the collection or use of their childs personal information. If you wish to stop the processing of your child's data, please follow these steps:
Steps to Stop Collection or Use:
Email Request:
Send an email to
privacy@bigalphagames.com
with the subject line "Stop Collection Request." Please include the following:
Your full name and relationship to the child.
Your child's account details, such as username or in-app ID.
In-App Option:
If available, open the app, navigate to the "Privacy Controls" section, and select the "Stop Data Collection" option.
2. Caregiver Right to Request Deletion of Your Child's Personal Information
Caregivers have the right to request that we remove all personal data collected from their child. If you wish to initiate a deletion request, please follow these steps:
Steps to Request Data Deletion:
Email Request:
Send an email to
privacy@bigalphagames.com
with the subject line
"Delete My Child's Data Request."
Please include:
Your child's username or relevant account details to help us identify the information to be deleted.
In-App Option:
Use the "Delete My Childs Data" option available in the app's Privacy Controls section, if applicable.
3. Caregiver Right to Review Your Child's Personal Information
Caregivers can request a detailed report of the personal information we have collected about their child. To review this data, follow these steps:
Steps to Request Data Review:
Email Request:
Contact us at
privacy@bigalphagames.com
with the subject line
"Review My Child's Data."
Include:
Proof of your identity and your relationship to the child.
Verification Process:
To ensure the security of your child's information, we may require you to verify your identity and relationship to the child. This verification prevents unauthorized actions.
Response Time:
Once we receive and verify your request, we will delete your child's personal information within 30 days. In some cases, certain data may need to be retained for legal purposes, such as fraud prevention or compliance.
Details Provided:
Upon verification, we will share the following information:
The types of personal data collected about your child.
The purpose for which the data was collected.
Details of any third parties with whom the data was shared.
Users Right to Lodge a Complaint
If you believe your data protection rights have been violated, you have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. These include:
The European Data Protection Board (EDPB).
Local data protection authorities in your jurisdiction.
For further guidance or to exercise your rights, please contact us at
privacy@bigalphagames.com
